From: ci <ci@local>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 16:48:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa: FMan PCD capability detection + CC steering stubs (M3-3b)

Observability-only stub for spec sec 3.5 (FMan PCD capability layer)
and sec 5.4 (CC steering API).  All productive paths return -ENOTSUPP;
the only runtime knob is the dpaa_fman_caps.force= module parameter
which allows developers to simulate "ucode 210 loaded" for unit testing
downstream consumers without flashing real ucode.

Adds:
  - drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.h    (new)
  - drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_fman_caps.c    (new)
  - CONFIG_DPAA_HW_CC_STEERING (default y, depends on FSL_DPAA_ETH)
  - priv->fman_caps + priv->hw_offload_unavailable in struct dpaa_priv
  - one-shot dpaa_fman_caps_log() emit from dpaa_eth_probe()
  - dpaa_stats_hwoffload[] ethtool array exposing the counter

Pairs with the 0079..0085 chain: identical observability-first cadence
(0083 was the xsk_rx_branch probe, 0084 was the BMan refill, 0085 was
the TX ZC submit/conf - 0086 is the HW-offload availability counter).

The CC steering API (fman_cc_tree_install/add_key/remove_key/destroy)
is fixed now so downstream consumers (af_xdp_pool qband-select, ASK2
flowtable bridge, future vyos-1x set-system-offload-classify CLI) can
wire calls today and gracefully degrade on ucode-106 silicon.  The
productive implementations land in follow-up patches per spec sec 5.4.

Spec: specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md v5.0 sec 3.5 + sec 5.4.

Signed-off-by: vyos-ls1046a-build CI <ci@local>
---
diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig
index 09c99af..0e52cda 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/Kconfig
@@ -20,4 +20,19 @@ config DPAA_FLAVOR_OPS
 	  and XSK pool management to dpaa_eth without touching core code.
 	  Safe to leave on: with no flavor module loaded, behaviour is unchanged.
 
+config DPAA_HW_CC_STEERING
+bool "DPAA: FMan PCD capability detection + CC steering stubs (M3-3b)"
+depends on FSL_DPAA_ETH
+default y
+help
+  Compile in the FMan PCD capability layer (dpaa_fman_get_caps,
+  FMAN_CAP_* bits) and the CC-steering stub API
+  (fman_cc_tree_install/add_key/remove_key/destroy) per
+  specs/dpaa1-afxdp-modernization-spec.md sec 3.5 and sec 5.4.
+  All stubs return -ENOTSUPP on mainline ucode 106 and bump
+  the hw_offload_unavailable ethtool counter.  Productive
+  implementations land in follow-up patches; the API is fixed
+  now so downstream consumers can wire calls today.
+  Safe to leave on: zero runtime cost without ucode 210.
+
 source "drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/af_xdp_pool/Kconfig"
